The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 June is 43,176 (4,997.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 June, there were 367 new confirmed cases (42.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 June, there were 258 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 42% (109 extra cases).
